            | My journey to becoming a software engineer began in a non-traditional environment: law school. While at Washington University in St. Louis School of Law, I focused a great deal of my legal education on startups and intellectual property. Learning about technology in the context of emerging growth companies got me interested in software development. After passing the California Bar Exam, I resolved to gain a software development skillset.
