            br
            br
            | I started pursuing my Masters in Computer and Information Technology at UPenn in Fall 2020. I decided to pursue a formal degree to expand my technical skillset to include not only web development, but also systems engineering, networking, machine learning, and more. 
            br
            br
            | In my current role at Stack Moxie, I'm helping to build an enterprise-grade, web-hook-based, no-code testing application for marketing professionals. While at Stack Moxie, I build entirely new features for the application that are deployed to consumers of the application. I have also contributed to product development, working closely with the founder and head of technology to come up with new features and how they will be implemented in the application for the best possible user experience. To get a feel for my capabilities, please check out some of the side projects I've completed as displayed on this site, visit my Github, or check out Stack Moxie! 
      
